  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Season the haddock fillets with salt, black pepper, and lemon juice.",
    "Heat the olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat and sear the haddock for 2-3 minutes per side.",
    "Transfer the skillet to the oven and bake for 8-10 minutes, or until the haddock is cooked through.",
    "While the haddock is baking, cook the pasta according to package instructions until al dente.",
    "In a large bowl, combine the cooked pasta, chopped basil, and grated parmesan cheese.",
    "Add the charred haddock to the bowl and toss to combine.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
